A grimy cadantine is a herb that has not yet been cleaned to make a cadantine. Grimy cadantines may be grown from a cadantine seed with a Farming level of 67, giving 120 Farming experience per herb harvested. It is also dropped by certain NPCs. Cleaning a grimy cadantine requires a Herblore level of 65 and gives 12.5 Herblore experience. Cadantines are used to make super defence potions with a Herblore level of 66.

Changes[edit | edit source]

Date Changes
12 August 2020
(update)

Composting grimy cadantine will now yield supercompost instead of regular compost.

9 March 2017
(update)

The item's value was increased from 1 to 22.

26 February 2015
(update)
  • The item was graphically updated to distinguish it from other grimy herbs.
  • The item was renamed from "Herb" to "Grimy cadantine".
  • The item was made tradeable on the Trading Post/Grand Exchange.
  • The “Identify” option was changed to a “Clean” option.
25 February 2013
(update)
  • The item was renamed from "Grimy cadantine" to "Herb".
  • The "Clean" option was changed to an "Identify" option.
22 February 2013
(update)
  • The item was renamed from "Herb" to "Grimy cadantine".
  • The "Identify" option was changed to a "Clean" option.
